## Mandatory completeness check (3 layers)

**Layer 1 — Pre-flight self-check** (in `<thinking>` before emit):

- Mode declared with `why: <phrase>`
- All fields for that mode present (no missing numbers)
- Each field has a value (not empty)
- `None`/`N/A`/`skipped` include a reason phrase
- Self-improvements + Agents present in C–G (non-`none` mandatory in G)
- Memory covers all systems (repo + vault + IDN + changelog as applicable)
- No per-tool lines in footer
- Mode-downgrade justified in `why:` if applicable

**Layer 2 — Visual completeness check:** count numbered lines match mode (D=8, C=6, etc.).

**Layer 3 — Cursor hook:** `afterAgentResponse` → `.cursor/hooks/validate-footer.ps1` (project) + `~/.cursor/hooks/validate-footer.ps1` (user global). Warns on mismatch; `failClosed: false`.

---

## Hard rules

- **Always** declare a mode at the top of the footer with `why: <phrase>`.
- **Always** include Self-improvements + Agents in modes C–G.
- **Always** include Memory in modes B–G.
- **Never** add per-tool lines to the footer (token savings, Sentry, RTK stats → body only).
- **Never** skip the footer for code, deploy, vault, IDN, memory, or subagent work.
- When hook returns `additional_context` warning, fix and re-emit.
